This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the segmentation of kidney tumors in CT images using a convolutional neural network. The use of innovative sampling techniques and cascaded training strategies also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the use of medical imaging data could also make it relevant to the medical imaging (cs.MS) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
